114static char *
115order_hostkeyalgs(char *host, struct sockaddr *hostaddr, u_short port)
116{
117 char *oavail, *avail, *first, *last, *alg, *hostname, *ret;
118 size_t maxlen;
119 struct hostkeys *hostkeys;
120 int ktype;
121 u_int i;
122
123 /* Find all hostkeys for this hostname */
124 get_hostfile_hostname_ipaddr(host, hostaddr, port, &hostname, NULL);
125 hostkeys = init_hostkeys();
126 for (i = 0; i < options.num_user_hostfiles; i++)
127 load_hostkeys(hostkeys, hostname, options.user_hostfiles[i]);
128 for (i = 0; i < options.num_system_hostfiles; i++)
129 load_hostkeys(hostkeys, hostname, options.system_hostfiles[i]);
130
131 oavail = avail = xstrdup(KEX_DEFAULT_PK_ALG);
132 maxlen = strlen(avail) + 1;
133 first = xmalloc(maxlen);
134 last = xmalloc(maxlen);
135 *first = *last = '\0';
136
137#define ALG_APPEND(to, from) \
138 do { \
139 if (*to != '\0') \
140 strlcat(to, ",", maxlen); \
141 strlcat(to, from, maxlen); \
142 } while (0)
143
144 while ((alg = strsep(&avail, ",")) && *alg != '\0') {
145 if ((ktype = sshkey_type_from_name(alg)) == KEY_UNSPEC)
146 fatal("%s: unknown alg %s", __func__, alg);
147 if (lookup_key_in_hostkeys_by_type(hostkeys,
148 sshkey_type_plain(ktype), NULL))
149 ALG_APPEND(first, alg);
150 else
151 ALG_APPEND(last, alg);
152 }
153#undef ALG_APPEND
154 xasprintf(&ret, "%s%s%s", first,
155 (*first == '\0' || *last == '\0') ? "" : ",", last);
156 if (*first != '\0')
157 debug3("%s: prefer hostkeyalgs: %s", __func__, first);
158
159 free(first);
160 free(last);
161 free(hostname);
162 free(oavail);
163 free_hostkeys(hostkeys);
164
165 return ret;
166}

168void
169ssh_kex2(struct ssh *ssh, char *host, struct sockaddr *hostaddr, u_short port)
170{
171 const char *myproposal[PROPOSAL_MAX] = { KEX_CLIENT };
172 char *s, *all_key;
173 int r;
174
175 xxx_host = host;
176 xxx_hostaddr = hostaddr;
177
178 if ((s = kex_names_cat(options.kex_algorithms, "ext-info-c")) == NULL)
179 fatal("%s: kex_names_cat", __func__);
180 myproposal[PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS] = compat_kex_proposal(s);
181 myproposal[PROPOSAL_ENC_ALGS_CTOS] =
182 compat_cipher_proposal(options.ciphers);
183 myproposal[PROPOSAL_ENC_ALGS_STOC] =
184 compat_cipher_proposal(options.ciphers);
185 myproposal[PROPOSAL_COMP_ALGS_CTOS] =
186 myproposal[PROPOSAL_COMP_ALGS_STOC] = options.compression ?
187 "zlib@openssh.com,zlib,none" : "none,zlib@openssh.com,zlib";
188 myproposal[PROPOSAL_MAC_ALGS_CTOS] =
189 myproposal[PROPOSAL_MAC_ALGS_STOC] = options.macs;
190 if (options.hostkeyalgorithms != NULL) {
191 all_key = sshkey_alg_list(0, 0, 1, ',');
192 if (kex_assemble_names(&options.hostkeyalgorithms,
193 KEX_DEFAULT_PK_ALG, all_key) != 0)
194 fatal("%s: kex_assemble_namelist", __func__);
195 free(all_key);
196 myproposal[PROPOSAL_SERVER_HOST_KEY_ALGS] =
197 compat_pkalg_proposal(options.hostkeyalgorithms);
198 } else {
199 /* Enforce default */
200 options.hostkeyalgorithms = xstrdup(KEX_DEFAULT_PK_ALG);
201 /* Prefer algorithms that we already have keys for */
202 myproposal[PROPOSAL_SERVER_HOST_KEY_ALGS] =
203 compat_pkalg_proposal(
204 order_hostkeyalgs(host, hostaddr, port));
205 }
206
207 if (options.rekey_limit || options.rekey_interval)
208 ssh_packet_set_rekey_limits(ssh, options.rekey_limit,
209 options.rekey_interval);
210
211 /* start key exchange */
212 if ((r = kex_setup(ssh, myproposal)) != 0)
213 fatal("kex_setup: %s", ssh_err(r));
214#ifdef WITH_OPENSSL
215 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_DH_GRP1_SHA1] = kex_gen_client;
216 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_DH_GRP14_SHA1] = kex_gen_client;
217 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_DH_GRP14_SHA256] = kex_gen_client;
218 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_DH_GRP16_SHA512] = kex_gen_client;
219 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_DH_GRP18_SHA512] = kex_gen_client;
220 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_DH_GEX_SHA1] = kexgex_client;
221 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_DH_GEX_SHA256] = kexgex_client;
222 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_ECDH_SHA2] = kex_gen_client;
223#endif
224 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_C25519_SHA256] = kex_gen_client;
225 ssh->kex->kex[KEX_KEM_SNTRUP4591761X25519_SHA512] = kex_gen_client;
226 ssh->kex->verify_host_key=&verify_host_key_callback;
227
228 ssh_dispatch_run_fatal(ssh, DISPATCH_BLOCK, &ssh->kex->done);
229
230 /* remove ext-info from the KEX proposals for rekeying */
231 myproposal[PROPOSAL_KEX_ALGS] =
232 compat_kex_proposal(options.kex_algorithms);
233 if ((r = kex_prop2buf(ssh->kex->my, myproposal)) != 0)
234 fatal("kex_prop2buf: %s", ssh_err(r));
235
236 session_id2 = ssh->kex->session_id;
237 session_id2_len = ssh->kex->session_id_len;
238
239#ifdef DEBUG_KEXDH
240 /* send 1st encrypted/maced/compressed message */
241 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_IGNORE)) != 0 ||
242 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, "markus")) != 0 ||
243 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0 ||
244 (r = ssh_packet_write_wait(ssh)) < 0)
245 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
246#endif
247}

386void
387ssh_userauth2(struct ssh *ssh, const char *local_user,
388 const char *server_user, char *host, Sensitive *sensitive)
389{
390 Authctxt authctxt;
391 int r;
392
393 if (options.challenge_response_authentication)
394 options.kbd_interactive_authentication = 1;
395 if (options.preferred_authentications == NULL)
396 options.preferred_authentications = authmethods_get();
397
398 /* setup authentication context */
399 memset(&authctxt, 0, sizeof(authctxt));
400 authctxt.server_user = server_user;
401 authctxt.local_user = local_user;
402 authctxt.host = host;
403 authctxt.service = "ssh-connection"; /* service name */
404 authctxt.success = 0;
405 authctxt.method = authmethod_lookup("none");
406 authctxt.authlist = NULL;
407 authctxt.methoddata = NULL;
408 authctxt.sensitive = sensitive;
409 authctxt.active_ktype = authctxt.oktypes = authctxt.ktypes = NULL;
410 authctxt.info_req_seen = 0;
411 authctxt.attempt_kbdint = 0;
412 authctxt.attempt_passwd = 0;
413#if GSSAPI
414 authctxt.gss_supported_mechs = NULL;
415 authctxt.mech_tried = 0;
416#endif
417 authctxt.agent_fd = -1;
418 pubkey_prepare(&authctxt);
419 if (authctxt.method == NULL) {
420 fatal("%s: internal error: cannot send userauth none request",
421 __func__);
422 }
423
424 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_SERVICE_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
425 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, "ssh-userauth")) != 0 ||
426 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
427 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
428
429 ssh->authctxt = &authctxt;
430 ssh_dispatch_init(ssh, &input_userauth_error);
431 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_EXT_INFO, &input_userauth_ext_info);
432 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_SERVICE_ACCEPT, &input_userauth_service_accept);
433 ssh_dispatch_run_fatal(ssh, DISPATCH_BLOCK, &authctxt.success); /* loop until success */
434 pubkey_cleanup(ssh);
435 ssh->authctxt = NULL;
436
437 ssh_dispatch_range(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_MIN, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_MAX, NULL);
438
439 /* if the user wants to use the none cipher do it */
440 /* post authentication and only if the right conditions are met */
441 /* both of the NONE commands must be true and there must be no */
442 /* tty allocated */
443 if ((options.none_switch == 1) && (options.none_enabled == 1))
444 {
445 if (tty_flag) /* no null on tty sessions */
446 {
447 /* requested NONE cipher when in a tty */
448 debug("Cannot switch to NONE cipher with tty allocated");
449 fprintf(stderr, "NONE cipher switch disabled when a TTY is allocated\n");
450 }
451 }
452 if (!authctxt.success)
453 fatal("Authentication failed.");
454
455 debug("Authentication succeeded (%s).", authctxt.method->name);
456}

458/* ARGSUSED */
459static int
460input_userauth_service_accept(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
461{
462 int r;
463
464 if (ssh_packet_remaining(ssh) > 0) {
465 char *reply;
466
467 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &reply, NULL)) != 0)
468 goto out;
469 debug2("service_accept: %s", reply);
470 free(reply);
471 } else {
472 debug2("buggy server: service_accept w/o service");
473 }
474 if ((r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0)
475 goto out;
476 debug("SSH2_MSG_SERVICE_ACCEPT received");
477
478 /* initial userauth request */
479 userauth_none(ssh);
480
481 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_EXT_INFO, &input_userauth_error);
482 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_SUCCESS, &input_userauth_success);
483 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_FAILURE, &input_userauth_failure);
484 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_BANNER, &input_userauth_banner);
485 r = 0;
486 out:
487 return r;
488}

497void
498userauth(struct ssh *ssh, char *authlist)
499{
500 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
501
502 if (authctxt->method != NULL && authctxt->method->cleanup != NULL)
503 authctxt->method->cleanup(ssh);
504
505 free(authctxt->methoddata);
506 authctxt->methoddata = NULL;
507 if (authlist == NULL) {
508 authlist = authctxt->authlist;
509 } else {
510 free(authctxt->authlist);
511 authctxt->authlist = authlist;
512 }
513 for (;;) {
514 Authmethod *method = authmethod_get(authlist);
515 if (method == NULL)
516 fatal("%s@%s: Permission denied (%s).",
517 authctxt->server_user, authctxt->host, authlist);
518 authctxt->method = method;
519
520 /* reset the per method handler */
521 ssh_dispatch_range(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_PER_METHOD_MIN,
522 SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_PER_METHOD_MAX, NULL);
523
524 /* and try new method */
525 if (method->userauth(ssh) != 0) {
526 debug2("we sent a %s packet, wait for reply", method->name);
527 break;
528 } else {
529 debug2("we did not send a packet, disable method");
530 method->enabled = NULL;
531 }
532 }
533}

545input_userauth_banner(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
546{
547 char *msg = NULL;
548 size_t len;
549 int r;
550
551 debug3("%s", __func__);
552 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &msg, &len)) != 0 ||
553 (r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, NULL, NULL)) != 0)
554 goto out;
555 if (len > 0 && options.log_level >= SYSLOG_LEVEL_INFO)
556 fmprintf(stderr, "%s", msg);
557 r = 0;
558 out:
559 free(msg);
560 return r;
561}

563/* ARGSUSED */
564static int
565input_userauth_success(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
566{
567 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
568
569 if (authctxt == NULL)
570 fatal("%s: no authentication context", __func__);
571 free(authctxt->authlist);
572 authctxt->authlist = NULL;
573 if (authctxt->method != NULL && authctxt->method->cleanup != NULL)
574 authctxt->method->cleanup(ssh);
575 free(authctxt->methoddata);
576 authctxt->methoddata = NULL;
577 authctxt->success = 1; /* break out */
578 return 0;
579}

596/* ARGSUSED */
597static int
598input_userauth_failure(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
599{
600 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
601 char *authlist = NULL;
602 u_char partial;
603 int r;
604
605 if (authctxt == NULL)
606 fatal("input_userauth_failure: no authentication context");
607
608 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &authlist, NULL)) != 0 ||
609 (r = sshpkt_get_u8(ssh, &partial)) != 0 ||
610 (r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0)
611 goto out;
612
613 if (partial != 0) {
614 verbose("Authenticated with partial success.");
615 /* reset state */
616 pubkey_reset(authctxt);
617 }
618 debug("Authentications that can continue: %s", authlist);
619
620 userauth(ssh, authlist);
621 authlist = NULL;
622 out:
623 free(authlist);
624 return 0;
625}

627/*
628 * Format an identity for logging including filename, key type, fingerprint
629 * and location (agent, etc.). Caller must free.
630 */
631static char *
632format_identity(Identity *id)
633{
634 char *fp = NULL, *ret = NULL;
635
636 if (id->key != NULL) {
637 fp = sshkey_fingerprint(id->key, options.fingerprint_hash,
638 SSH_FP_DEFAULT);
639 }
640 xasprintf(&ret, "%s %s%s%s%s%s%s",
641 id->filename,
642 id->key ? sshkey_type(id->key) : "", id->key ? " " : "",
643 fp ? fp : "",
644 id->userprovided ? " explicit" : "",
645 (id->key && (id->key->flags & SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT)) ? " token" : "",
646 id->agent_fd != -1 ? " agent" : "");
647 free(fp);
648 return ret;
649}

651/* ARGSUSED */
652static int
653input_userauth_pk_ok(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
654{
655 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
656 struct sshkey *key = NULL;
657 Identity *id = NULL;
658 int pktype, found = 0, sent = 0;
659 size_t blen;
660 char *pkalg = NULL, *fp = NULL, *ident = NULL;
661 u_char *pkblob = NULL;
662 int r;
663
664 if (authctxt == NULL)
665 fatal("input_userauth_pk_ok: no authentication context");
666
667 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &pkalg, NULL)) != 0 ||
668 (r = sshpkt_get_string(ssh, &pkblob, &blen)) != 0 ||
669 (r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0)
670 goto done;
671
672 if ((pktype = sshkey_type_from_name(pkalg)) == KEY_UNSPEC) {
673 debug("%s: server sent unknown pkalg %s", __func__, pkalg);
674 goto done;
675 }
676 if ((r = sshkey_from_blob(pkblob, blen, &key)) != 0) {
677 debug("no key from blob. pkalg %s: %s", pkalg, ssh_err(r));
678 goto done;
679 }
680 if (key->type != pktype) {
681 error("input_userauth_pk_ok: type mismatch "
682 "for decoded key (received %d, expected %d)",
683 key->type, pktype);
684 goto done;
685 }
686
687 /*
688 * search keys in the reverse order, because last candidate has been
689 * moved to the end of the queue. this also avoids confusion by
690 * duplicate keys
691 */
692 TAILQ_FOREACH_REVERSE(id, &authctxt->keys, idlist, next) {
693 if (sshkey_equal(key, id->key)) {
694 found = 1;
695 break;
696 }
697 }
698 if (!found || id == NULL) {
699 fp = sshkey_fingerprint(key, options.fingerprint_hash,
700 SSH_FP_DEFAULT);
701 error("%s: server replied with unknown key: %s %s", __func__,
702 sshkey_type(key), fp == NULL ? "<ERROR>" : fp);
703 goto done;
704 }
705 ident = format_identity(id);
706 debug("Server accepts key: %s", ident);
707 sent = sign_and_send_pubkey(ssh, id);
708 r = 0;
709 done:
710 sshkey_free(key);
711 free(ident);
712 free(fp);
713 free(pkalg);
714 free(pkblob);
715
716 /* try another method if we did not send a packet */
717 if (r == 0 && sent == 0)
718 userauth(ssh, NULL);
719 return r;
720}

722#ifdef GSSAPI
723static int
724userauth_gssapi(struct ssh *ssh)
725{
726 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
727 Gssctxt *gssctxt = NULL;
728 OM_uint32 min;
729 int r, ok = 0;
730 gss_OID mech = NULL;
731
732 /* Try one GSSAPI method at a time, rather than sending them all at
733 * once. */
734
735 if (authctxt->gss_supported_mechs == NULL)
736 gss_indicate_mechs(&min, &authctxt->gss_supported_mechs);
737
738 /* Check to see whether the mechanism is usable before we offer it */
739 while (authctxt->mech_tried < authctxt->gss_supported_mechs->count &&
740 !ok) {
741 mech = &authctxt->gss_supported_mechs->
742 elements[authctxt->mech_tried];
743 /* My DER encoding requires length<128 */
744 if (mech->length < 128 && ssh_gssapi_check_mechanism(&gssctxt,
745 mech, authctxt->host)) {
746 ok = 1; /* Mechanism works */
747 } else {
748 authctxt->mech_tried++;
749 }
750 }
751
752 if (!ok || mech == NULL)
753 return 0;
754
755 authctxt->methoddata=(void *)gssctxt;
756
757 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
758 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
759 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
760 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
761 (r = sshpkt_put_u32(ssh, 1)) != 0 ||
762 (r = sshpkt_put_u32(ssh, (mech->length) + 2)) != 0 ||
763 (r = sshpkt_put_u8(ssh, SSH_GSS_OIDTYPE)) != 0 ||
764 (r = sshpkt_put_u8(ssh, mech->length)) != 0 ||
765 (r = sshpkt_put(ssh, mech->elements, mech->length)) != 0 ||
766 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
767 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
768
769 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_RESPONSE, &input_gssapi_response);
770 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_TOKEN, &input_gssapi_token);
771 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_ERROR, &input_gssapi_error);
772 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_ERRTOK, &input_gssapi_errtok);
773
774 authctxt->mech_tried++; /* Move along to next candidate */
775
776 return 1;
777}

792static OM_uint32
793process_gssapi_token(struct ssh *ssh, gss_buffer_t recv_tok)
794{
795 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
796 Gssctxt *gssctxt = authctxt->methoddata;
797 gss_buffer_desc send_tok = GSS_C_EMPTY_BUFFER;
798 gss_buffer_desc mic = GSS_C_EMPTY_BUFFER;
799 gss_buffer_desc gssbuf;
800 OM_uint32 status, ms, flags;
801 int r;
802
803 status = ssh_gssapi_init_ctx(gssctxt, options.gss_deleg_creds,
804 recv_tok, &send_tok, &flags);
805
806 if (send_tok.length > 0) {
807 u_char type = GSS_ERROR(status) ?
808 SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_ERRTOK :
809 SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_TOKEN;
810
811 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, type)) != 0 ||
812 (r = sshpkt_put_string(ssh, send_tok.value,
813 send_tok.length)) != 0 ||
814 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
815 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
816
817 gss_release_buffer(&ms, &send_tok);
818 }
819
820 if (status == GSS_S_COMPLETE) {
821 /* send either complete or MIC, depending on mechanism */
822 if (!(flags & GSS_C_INTEG_FLAG)) {
823 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh,
824 SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_EXCHANGE_COMPLETE)) != 0 ||
825 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
826 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
827 } else {
828 struct sshbuf *b;
829
830 if ((b = sshbuf_new()) == NULL)
831 fatal("%s: sshbuf_new failed", __func__);
832 ssh_gssapi_buildmic(b, authctxt->server_user,
833 authctxt->service, "gssapi-with-mic");
834
835 if ((gssbuf.value = sshbuf_mutable_ptr(b)) == NULL)
836 fatal("%s: sshbuf_mutable_ptr failed", __func__);
837 gssbuf.length = sshbuf_len(b);
838
839 status = ssh_gssapi_sign(gssctxt, &gssbuf, &mic);
840
841 if (!GSS_ERROR(status)) {
842 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh,
843 SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_GSSAPI_MIC)) != 0 ||
844 (r = sshpkt_put_string(ssh, mic.value,
845 mic.length)) != 0 ||
846 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
847 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
848 }
849
850 sshbuf_free(b);
851 gss_release_buffer(&ms, &mic);
852 }
853 }
854
855 return status;
856}

858/* ARGSUSED */
859static int
860input_gssapi_response(int type, u_int32_t plen, struct ssh *ssh)
861{
862 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
863 Gssctxt *gssctxt;
864 size_t oidlen;
865 u_char *oidv = NULL;
866 int r;
867
868 if (authctxt == NULL)
869 fatal("input_gssapi_response: no authentication context");
870 gssctxt = authctxt->methoddata;
871
872 /* Setup our OID */
873 if ((r = sshpkt_get_string(ssh, &oidv, &oidlen)) != 0)
874 goto done;
875
876 if (oidlen <= 2 ||
877 oidv[0] != SSH_GSS_OIDTYPE ||
878 oidv[1] != oidlen - 2) {
879 debug("Badly encoded mechanism OID received");
880 userauth(ssh, NULL);
881 goto ok;
882 }
883
884 if (!ssh_gssapi_check_oid(gssctxt, oidv + 2, oidlen - 2))
885 fatal("Server returned different OID than expected");
886
887 if ((r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0)
888 goto done;
889
890 if (GSS_ERROR(process_gssapi_token(ssh, GSS_C_NO_BUFFER))) {
891 /* Start again with next method on list */
892 debug("Trying to start again");
893 userauth(ssh, NULL);
894 goto ok;
895 }
896 ok:
897 r = 0;
898 done:
899 free(oidv);
900 return r;
901}

903/* ARGSUSED */
904static int
905input_gssapi_token(int type, u_int32_t plen, struct ssh *ssh)
906{
907 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
908 gss_buffer_desc recv_tok;
909 u_char *p = NULL;
910 size_t len;
911 OM_uint32 status;
912 int r;
913
914 if (authctxt == NULL)
915 fatal("input_gssapi_response: no authentication context");
916
917 if ((r = sshpkt_get_string(ssh, &p, &len)) != 0 ||
918 (r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0)
919 goto out;
920
921 recv_tok.value = p;
922 recv_tok.length = len;
923 status = process_gssapi_token(ssh, &recv_tok);
924
925 /* Start again with the next method in the list */
926 if (GSS_ERROR(status)) {
927 userauth(ssh, NULL);
928 /* ok */
929 }
930 r = 0;
931 out:
932 free(p);
933 return r;
934}

936/* ARGSUSED */
937static int
938input_gssapi_errtok(int type, u_int32_t plen, struct ssh *ssh)
939{
940 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
941 Gssctxt *gssctxt;
942 gss_buffer_desc send_tok = GSS_C_EMPTY_BUFFER;
943 gss_buffer_desc recv_tok;
944 OM_uint32 ms;
945 u_char *p = NULL;
946 size_t len;
947 int r;
948
949 if (authctxt == NULL)
950 fatal("input_gssapi_response: no authentication context");
951 gssctxt = authctxt->methoddata;
952
953 if ((r = sshpkt_get_string(ssh, &p, &len)) != 0 ||
954 (r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0) {
955 free(p);
956 return r;
957 }
958
959 /* Stick it into GSSAPI and see what it says */
960 recv_tok.value = p;
961 recv_tok.length = len;
962 (void)ssh_gssapi_init_ctx(gssctxt, options.gss_deleg_creds,
963 &recv_tok, &send_tok, NULL);
964 free(p);
965 gss_release_buffer(&ms, &send_tok);
966
967 /* Server will be returning a failed packet after this one */
968 return 0;
969}

1009static int
1010userauth_passwd(struct ssh *ssh)
1011{
1012 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
1013 char *password, *prompt = NULL;
1014 const char *host = options.host_key_alias ? options.host_key_alias :
1015 authctxt->host;
1016 int r;
1017
1018 if (authctxt->attempt_passwd++ >= options.number_of_password_prompts)
1019 return 0;
1020
1021 if (authctxt->attempt_passwd != 1)
1022 error("Permission denied, please try again.");
1023
1024 xasprintf(&prompt, "%s@%s's password: ", authctxt->server_user, host);
1025 password = read_passphrase(prompt, 0);
1026 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
1027 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
1028 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
1029 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
1030 (r = sshpkt_put_u8(ssh, 0)) != 0 ||
1031 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, password)) != 0 ||
1032 (r = sshpkt_add_padding(ssh, 64)) != 0 ||
1033 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
1034 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1035
1036 free(prompt);
1037 if (password != NULL)
1038 freezero(password, strlen(password));
1039
1040 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_PASSWD_CHANGEREQ,
1041 &input_userauth_passwd_changereq);
1042
1043 return 1;
1044}

1046/*
1047 * parse PASSWD_CHANGEREQ, prompt user and send SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST
1048 */
1049/* ARGSUSED */
1050static int
1051input_userauth_passwd_changereq(int type, u_int32_t seqnr, struct ssh *ssh)
1052{
1053 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
1054 char *info = NULL, *lang = NULL, *password = NULL, *retype = NULL;
1055 char prompt[256];
1056 const char *host;
1057 int r;
1058
1059 debug2("input_userauth_passwd_changereq");
1060
1061 if (authctxt == NULL)
1062 fatal("input_userauth_passwd_changereq: "
1063 "no authentication context");
1064 host = options.host_key_alias ? options.host_key_alias : authctxt->host;
1065
1066 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &info, NULL)) != 0 ||
1067 (r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &lang, NULL)) != 0)
1068 goto out;
1069 if (strlen(info) > 0)
1070 logit("%s", info);
1071 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
1072 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
1073 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
1074 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
1075 (r = sshpkt_put_u8(ssh, 1)) != 0) /* additional info */
1076 goto out;
1077
1078 snprintf(prompt, sizeof(prompt),
1079 "Enter %.30s@%.128s's old password: ",
1080 authctxt->server_user, host);
1081 password = read_passphrase(prompt, 0);
1082 if ((r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, password)) != 0)
1083 goto out;
1084
1085 freezero(password, strlen(password));
1086 password = NULL;
1087 while (password == NULL) {
1088 snprintf(prompt, sizeof(prompt),
1089 "Enter %.30s@%.128s's new password: ",
1090 authctxt->server_user, host);
1091 password = read_passphrase(prompt, RP_ALLOW_EOF);
1092 if (password == NULL) {
1093 /* bail out */
1094 r = 0;
1095 goto out;
1096 }
1097 snprintf(prompt, sizeof(prompt),
1098 "Retype %.30s@%.128s's new password: ",
1099 authctxt->server_user, host);
1100 retype = read_passphrase(prompt, 0);
1101 if (strcmp(password, retype) != 0) {
1102 freezero(password, strlen(password));
1103 logit("Mismatch; try again, EOF to quit.");
1104 password = NULL;
1105 }
1106 freezero(retype, strlen(retype));
1107 }
1108 if ((r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, password)) != 0 ||
1109 (r = sshpkt_add_padding(ssh, 64)) != 0 ||
1110 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
1111 goto out;
1112
1113 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_PASSWD_CHANGEREQ,
1114 &input_userauth_passwd_changereq);
1115 r = 0;
1116 out:
1117 if (password)
1118 freezero(password, strlen(password));
1119 free(info);
1120 free(lang);
1121 return r;
1122}

1124/*
1125 * Select an algorithm for publickey signatures.
1126 * Returns algorithm (caller must free) or NULL if no mutual algorithm found.
1127 *
1128 * Call with ssh==NULL to ignore server-sig-algs extension list and
1129 * only attempt with the key's base signature type.
1130 */
1131static char *
1132key_sig_algorithm(struct ssh *ssh, const struct sshkey *key)
1133{
1134 char *allowed, *oallowed, *cp, *tmp, *alg = NULL;
1135
1136 /*
1137 * The signature algorithm will only differ from the key algorithm
1138 * for RSA keys/certs and when the server advertises support for
1139 * newer (SHA2) algorithms.
1140 */
1141 if (ssh == NULL || ssh->kex->server_sig_algs == NULL ||
1142 (key->type != KEY_RSA && key->type != KEY_RSA_CERT) ||
1143 (key->type == KEY_RSA_CERT && (datafellows & SSH_BUG_SIGTYPE))) {
1144 /* Filter base key signature alg against our configuration */
1145 return match_list(sshkey_ssh_name(key),
1146 options.pubkey_key_types, NULL);
1147 }
1148
1149 /*
1150 * For RSA keys/certs, since these might have a different sig type:
1151 * find the first entry in PubkeyAcceptedKeyTypes of the right type
1152 * that also appears in the supported signature algorithms list from
1153 * the server.
1154 */
1155 oallowed = allowed = xstrdup(options.pubkey_key_types);
1156 while ((cp = strsep(&allowed, ",")) != NULL) {
1157 if (sshkey_type_from_name(cp) != key->type)
1158 continue;
1159 tmp = match_list(sshkey_sigalg_by_name(cp), ssh->kex->server_sig_algs, NULL);
1160 if (tmp != NULL)
1161 alg = xstrdup(cp);
1162 free(tmp);
1163 if (alg != NULL)
1164 break;
1165 }
1166 free(oallowed);
1167 return alg;
1168}
1169
1170static int
1171identity_sign(struct identity *id, u_char **sigp, size_t *lenp,
1172 const u_char *data, size_t datalen, u_int compat, const char *alg)
1173{
1174 struct sshkey *prv;
1175 int r;
1176
1177 /* The agent supports this key. */
1178 if (id->key != NULL && id->agent_fd != -1) {
1179 return ssh_agent_sign(id->agent_fd, id->key, sigp, lenp,
1180 data, datalen, alg, compat);
1181 }
1182
1183 /*
1184 * We have already loaded the private key or the private key is
1185 * stored in external hardware.
1186 */
1187 if (id->key != NULL &&
1188 (id->isprivate || (id->key->flags & SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT))) {
1189 if ((r = sshkey_sign(id->key, sigp, lenp, data, datalen,
1190 alg, compat)) != 0)
1191 return r;
1192 /*
1193 * PKCS#11 tokens may not support all signature algorithms,
1194 * so check what we get back.
1195 */
1196 if ((r = sshkey_check_sigtype(*sigp, *lenp, alg)) != 0)
1197 return r;
1198 return 0;
1199 }
1200
1201 /* Load the private key from the file. */
1202 if ((prv = load_identity_file(id)) == NULL)
1203 return SSH_ERR_KEY_NOT_FOUND;
1204 if (id->key != NULL && !sshkey_equal_public(prv, id->key)) {
1205 error("%s: private key %s contents do not match public",
1206 __func__, id->filename);
1207 return SSH_ERR_KEY_NOT_FOUND;
1208 }
1209 r = sshkey_sign(prv, sigp, lenp, data, datalen, alg, compat);
1210 sshkey_free(prv);
1211 return r;
1212}

1214static int
1215id_filename_matches(Identity *id, Identity *private_id)
1216{
1217 const char *suffixes[] = { ".pub", "-cert.pub", NULL };
1218 size_t len = strlen(id->filename), plen = strlen(private_id->filename);
1219 size_t i, slen;
1220
1221 if (strcmp(id->filename, private_id->filename) == 0)
1222 return 1;
1223 for (i = 0; suffixes[i]; i++) {
1224 slen = strlen(suffixes[i]);
1225 if (len > slen && plen == len - slen &&
1226 strcmp(id->filename + (len - slen), suffixes[i]) == 0 &&
1227 memcmp(id->filename, private_id->filename, plen) == 0)
1228 return 1;
1229 }
1230 return 0;
1231}
1232
1233static int
1234sign_and_send_pubkey(struct ssh *ssh, Identity *id)
1235{
1236 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
1237 struct sshbuf *b = NULL;
1238 Identity *private_id, *sign_id = NULL;
1239 u_char *signature = NULL;
1240 size_t slen = 0, skip = 0;
1241 int r, fallback_sigtype, sent = 0;
1242 char *alg = NULL, *fp = NULL;
1243 const char *loc = "";
1244
1245 if ((fp = sshkey_fingerprint(id->key, options.fingerprint_hash,
1246 SSH_FP_DEFAULT)) == NULL)
1247 return 0;
1248
1249 debug3("%s: %s %s", __func__, sshkey_type(id->key), fp);
1250
1251 /*
1252 * If the key is an certificate, try to find a matching private key
1253 * and use it to complete the signature.
1254 * If no such private key exists, fall back to trying the certificate
1255 * key itself in case it has a private half already loaded.
1256 * This will try to set sign_id to the private key that will perform
1257 * the signature.
1258 */
1259 if (sshkey_is_cert(id->key)) {
1260 TAILQ_FOREACH(private_id, &authctxt->keys, next) {
1261 if (sshkey_equal_public(id->key, private_id->key) &&
1262 id->key->type != private_id->key->type) {
1263 sign_id = private_id;
1264 break;
1265 }
1266 }
1267 /*
1268 * Exact key matches are preferred, but also allow
1269 * filename matches for non-PKCS#11/agent keys that
1270 * didn't load public keys. This supports the case
1271 * of keeping just a private key file and public
1272 * certificate on disk.
1273 */
1274 if (sign_id == NULL &&
1275 !id->isprivate && id->agent_fd == -1 &&
1276 (id->key->flags & SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT) == 0) {
1277 TAILQ_FOREACH(private_id, &authctxt->keys, next) {
1278 if (private_id->key == NULL &&
1279 id_filename_matches(id, private_id)) {
1280 sign_id = private_id;
1281 break;
1282 }
1283 }
1284 }
1285 if (sign_id != NULL) {
1286 debug2("%s: using private key \"%s\"%s for "
1287 "certificate", __func__, id->filename,
1288 id->agent_fd != -1 ? " from agent" : "");
1289 } else {
1290 debug("%s: no separate private key for certificate "
1291 "\"%s\"", __func__, id->filename);
1292 }
1293 }
1294
1295 /*
1296 * If the above didn't select another identity to do the signing
1297 * then default to the one we started with.
1298 */
1299 if (sign_id == NULL)
1300 sign_id = id;
1301
1302 /* assemble and sign data */
1303 for (fallback_sigtype = 0; fallback_sigtype <= 1; fallback_sigtype++) {
1304 free(alg);
1305 slen = 0;
1306 signature = NULL;
1307 if ((alg = key_sig_algorithm(fallback_sigtype ? NULL : ssh,
1308 id->key)) == NULL) {
1309 error("%s: no mutual signature supported", __func__);
1310 goto out;
1311 }
1312 debug3("%s: signing using %s", __func__, alg);
1313
1314 sshbuf_free(b);
1315 if ((b = sshbuf_new()) == NULL)
1316 fatal("%s: sshbuf_new failed", __func__);
1317 if (datafellows & SSH_OLD_SESSIONID) {
1318 if ((r = sshbuf_put(b, session_id2,
1319 session_id2_len)) != 0) {
1320 fatal("%s: sshbuf_put: %s",
1321 __func__, ssh_err(r));
1322 }
1323 } else {
1324 if ((r = sshbuf_put_string(b, session_id2,
1325 session_id2_len)) != 0) {
1326 fatal("%s: sshbuf_put_string: %s",
1327 __func__, ssh_err(r));
1328 }
1329 }
1330 skip = sshbuf_len(b);
1331 if ((r = sshbuf_put_u8(b, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
1332 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
1333 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
1334 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
1335 (r = sshbuf_put_u8(b, 1)) != 0 ||
1336 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, alg)) != 0 ||
1337 (r = sshkey_puts(id->key, b)) != 0) {
1338 fatal("%s: assemble signed data: %s",
1339 __func__, ssh_err(r));
1340 }
1341
1342 /* generate signature */
1343 r = identity_sign(sign_id, &signature, &slen,
1344 sshbuf_ptr(b), sshbuf_len(b), datafellows, alg);
1345 if (r == 0)
1346 break;
1347 else if (r == SSH_ERR_KEY_NOT_FOUND)
1348 goto out; /* soft failure */
1349 else if (r == SSH_ERR_SIGN_ALG_UNSUPPORTED &&
1350 !fallback_sigtype) {
1351 if (sign_id->agent_fd != -1)
1352 loc = "agent ";
1353 else if ((sign_id->key->flags & SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT) != 0)
1354 loc = "token ";
1355 logit("%skey %s %s returned incorrect signature type",
1356 loc, sshkey_type(id->key), fp);
1357 continue;
1358 }
1359 error("%s: signing failed: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1360 goto out;
1361 }
1362 if (slen == 0 || signature == NULL) /* shouldn't happen */
1363 fatal("%s: no signature", __func__);
1364
1365 /* append signature */
1366 if ((r = sshbuf_put_string(b, signature, slen)) != 0)
1367 fatal("%s: append signature: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1368
1369#ifdef DEBUG_PK
1370 sshbuf_dump(b, stderr);
1371#endif
1372 /* skip session id and packet type */
1373 if ((r = sshbuf_consume(b, skip + 1)) != 0)
1374 fatal("%s: consume: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1375
1376 /* put remaining data from buffer into packet */
1377 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
1378 (r = sshpkt_putb(ssh, b)) != 0 ||
1379 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
1380 fatal("%s: enqueue request: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1381
1382 /* success */
1383 sent = 1;
1384
1385 out:
1386 free(fp);
1387 free(alg);
1388 sshbuf_free(b);
1389 freezero(signature, slen);
1390 return sent;
1391}
1392
1393static int
1394send_pubkey_test(struct ssh *ssh, Identity *id)
1395{
1396 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
1397 u_char *blob = NULL;
1398 char *alg = NULL;
1399 size_t bloblen;
1400 u_int have_sig = 0;
1401 int sent = 0, r;
1402
1403 if ((alg = key_sig_algorithm(ssh, id->key)) == NULL) {
1404 debug("%s: no mutual signature algorithm", __func__);
1405 goto out;
1406 }
1407
1408 if ((r = sshkey_to_blob(id->key, &blob, &bloblen)) != 0) {
1409 /* we cannot handle this key */
1410 debug3("%s: cannot handle key", __func__);
1411 goto out;
1412 }
1413 /* register callback for USERAUTH_PK_OK message */
1414 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_PK_OK, &input_userauth_pk_ok);
1415
1416 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
1417 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
1418 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
1419 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
1420 (r = sshpkt_put_u8(ssh, have_sig)) != 0 ||
1421 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, alg)) != 0 ||
1422 (r = sshpkt_put_string(ssh, blob, bloblen)) != 0 ||
1423 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
1424 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1425 sent = 1;
1426
1427 out:
1428 free(alg);
1429 free(blob);
1430 return sent;
1431}

1433static struct sshkey *
1434load_identity_file(Identity *id)
1435{
1436 struct sshkey *private = NULL;
1437 char prompt[300], *passphrase, *comment;
1438 int r, perm_ok = 0, quit = 0, i;
1439 struct stat st;
1440
1441 if (stat(id->filename, &st) < 0) {
1442 (id->userprovided ? logit : debug3)("no such identity: %s: %s",
1443 id->filename, strerror(errno));
1444 return NULL;
1445 }
1446 snprintf(prompt, sizeof prompt,
1447 "Enter passphrase for key '%.100s': ", id->filename);
1448 for (i = 0; i <= options.number_of_password_prompts; i++) {
1449 if (i == 0)
1450 passphrase = xstrdup("");
1451 else {
1452 passphrase = read_passphrase(prompt, 0);
1453 if (*passphrase == '\0') {
1454 debug2("no passphrase given, try next key");
1455 free(passphrase);
1456 break;
1457 }
1458 }
1459 switch ((r = sshkey_load_private_type(KEY_UNSPEC, id->filename,
1460 passphrase, &private, &comment, &perm_ok))) {
1461 case 0:
1462 break;
1463 case SSH_ERR_KEY_WRONG_PASSPHRASE:
1464 if (options.batch_mode) {
1465 quit = 1;
1466 break;
1467 }
1468 if (i != 0)
1469 debug2("bad passphrase given, try again...");
1470 break;
1471 case SSH_ERR_SYSTEM_ERROR:
1472 if (errno == ENOENT) {
1473 debug2("Load key \"%s\": %s",
1474 id->filename, ssh_err(r));
1475 quit = 1;
1476 break;
1477 }
1478 /* FALLTHROUGH */
1479 default:
1480 error("Load key \"%s\": %s", id->filename, ssh_err(r));
1481 quit = 1;
1482 break;
1483 }
1484 if (!quit && private != NULL && id->agent_fd == -1 &&
1485 !(id->key && id->isprivate))
1486 maybe_add_key_to_agent(id->filename, private, comment,
1487 passphrase);
1488 if (i > 0)
1489 freezero(passphrase, strlen(passphrase));
1490 free(comment);
1491 if (private != NULL || quit)
1492 break;
1493 }
1494 return private;
1495}
1496
1497static int
1498key_type_allowed_by_config(struct sshkey *key)
1499{
1500 if (match_pattern_list(sshkey_ssh_name(key),
1501 options.pubkey_key_types, 0) == 1)
1502 return 1;
1503
1504 /* RSA keys/certs might be allowed by alternate signature types */
1505 switch (key->type) {
1506 case KEY_RSA:
1507 if (match_pattern_list("rsa-sha2-512",
1508 options.pubkey_key_types, 0) == 1)
1509 return 1;
1510 if (match_pattern_list("rsa-sha2-256",
1511 options.pubkey_key_types, 0) == 1)
1512 return 1;
1513 break;
1514 case KEY_RSA_CERT:
1515 if (match_pattern_list("rsa-sha2-512-cert-v01@openssh.com",
1516 options.pubkey_key_types, 0) == 1)
1517 return 1;
1518 if (match_pattern_list("rsa-sha2-256-cert-v01@openssh.com",
1519 options.pubkey_key_types, 0) == 1)
1520 return 1;
1521 break;
1522 }
1523 return 0;
1524}
1525
1526
1527/*
1528 * try keys in the following order:
1529 * 1. certificates listed in the config file
1530 * 2. other input certificates
1531 * 3. agent keys that are found in the config file
1532 * 4. other agent keys
1533 * 5. keys that are only listed in the config file
1534 */
1535static void
1536pubkey_prepare(Authctxt *authctxt)
1537{
1538 struct identity *id, *id2, *tmp;
1539 struct idlist agent, files, *preferred;
1540 struct sshkey *key;
1541 int agent_fd = -1, i, r, found;
1542 size_t j;
1543 struct ssh_identitylist *idlist;
1544 char *ident;
1545
1546 TAILQ_INIT(&agent); /* keys from the agent */
1547 TAILQ_INIT(&files); /* keys from the config file */
1548 preferred = &authctxt->keys;
1549 TAILQ_INIT(preferred); /* preferred order of keys */
1550
1551 /* list of keys stored in the filesystem and PKCS#11 */
1552 for (i = 0; i < options.num_identity_files; i++) {
1553 key = options.identity_keys[i];
1554 if (key && key->cert && key->cert->type != SSH2_CERT_TYPE_USER)
1555 continue;
1556 options.identity_keys[i] = NULL;
1557 id = xcalloc(1, sizeof(*id));
1558 id->agent_fd = -1;
1559 id->key = key;
1560 id->filename = xstrdup(options.identity_files[i]);
1561 id->userprovided = options.identity_file_userprovided[i];
1562 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&files, id, next);
1563 }
1564 /* list of certificates specified by user */
1565 for (i = 0; i < options.num_certificate_files; i++) {
1566 key = options.certificates[i];
1567 if (!sshkey_is_cert(key) || key->cert == NULL ||
1568 key->cert->type != SSH2_CERT_TYPE_USER)
1569 continue;
1570 id = xcalloc(1, sizeof(*id));
1571 id->agent_fd = -1;
1572 id->key = key;
1573 id->filename = xstrdup(options.certificate_files[i]);
1574 id->userprovided = options.certificate_file_userprovided[i];
1575 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(preferred, id, next);
1576 }
1577 /* list of keys supported by the agent */
1578 if ((r = ssh_get_authentication_socket(&agent_fd)) != 0) {
1579 if (r != SSH_ERR_AGENT_NOT_PRESENT)
1580 debug("%s: ssh_get_authentication_socket: %s",
1581 __func__, ssh_err(r));
1582 } else if ((r = ssh_fetch_identitylist(agent_fd, &idlist)) != 0) {
1583 if (r != SSH_ERR_AGENT_NO_IDENTITIES)
1584 debug("%s: ssh_fetch_identitylist: %s",
1585 __func__, ssh_err(r));
1586 close(agent_fd);
1587 } else {
1588 for (j = 0; j < idlist->nkeys; j++) {
1589 found = 0;
1590 TAILQ_FOREACH(id, &files, next) {
1591 /*
1592 * agent keys from the config file are
1593 * preferred
1594 */
1595 if (sshkey_equal(idlist->keys[j], id->key)) {
1596 TAILQ_REMOVE(&files, id, next);
1597 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(preferred, id, next);
1598 id->agent_fd = agent_fd;
1599 found = 1;
1600 break;
1601 }
1602 }
1603 if (!found && !options.identities_only) {
1604 id = xcalloc(1, sizeof(*id));
1605 /* XXX "steals" key/comment from idlist */
1606 id->key = idlist->keys[j];
1607 id->filename = idlist->comments[j];
1608 idlist->keys[j] = NULL;
1609 idlist->comments[j] = NULL;
1610 id->agent_fd = agent_fd;
1611 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&agent, id, next);
1612 }
1613 }
1614 ssh_free_identitylist(idlist);
1615 /* append remaining agent keys */
1616 for (id = TAILQ_FIRST(&agent); id; id = TAILQ_FIRST(&agent)) {
1617 TAILQ_REMOVE(&agent, id, next);
1618 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(preferred, id, next);
1619 }
1620 authctxt->agent_fd = agent_fd;
1621 }
1622 /* Prefer PKCS11 keys that are explicitly listed */
1623 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(id, &files, next, tmp) {
1624 if (id->key == NULL || (id->key->flags & SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT) == 0)
1625 continue;
1626 found = 0;
1627 TAILQ_FOREACH(id2, &files, next) {
1628 if (id2->key == NULL ||
1629 (id2->key->flags & SSHKEY_FLAG_EXT) == 0)
1630 continue;
1631 if (sshkey_equal(id->key, id2->key)) {
1632 TAILQ_REMOVE(&files, id, next);
1633 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(preferred, id, next);
1634 found = 1;
1635 break;
1636 }
1637 }
1638 /* If IdentitiesOnly set and key not found then don't use it */
1639 if (!found && options.identities_only) {
1640 TAILQ_REMOVE(&files, id, next);
1641 freezero(id, sizeof(*id));
1642 }
1643 }
1644 /* append remaining keys from the config file */
1645 for (id = TAILQ_FIRST(&files); id; id = TAILQ_FIRST(&files)) {
1646 TAILQ_REMOVE(&files, id, next);
1647 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(preferred, id, next);
1648 }
1649 /* finally, filter by PubkeyAcceptedKeyTypes */
1650 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(id, preferred, next, id2) {
1651 if (id->key != NULL && !key_type_allowed_by_config(id->key)) {
1652 debug("Skipping %s key %s - "
1653 "not in PubkeyAcceptedKeyTypes",
1654 sshkey_ssh_name(id->key), id->filename);
1655 TAILQ_REMOVE(preferred, id, next);
1656 sshkey_free(id->key);
1657 free(id->filename);
1658 memset(id, 0, sizeof(*id));
1659 continue;
1660 }
1661 }
1662 /* List the keys we plan on using */
1663 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(id, preferred, next, id2) {
1664 ident = format_identity(id);
1665 debug("Will attempt key: %s", ident);
1666 free(ident);
1667 }
1668 debug2("%s: done", __func__);
1669}

1671static void
1672pubkey_cleanup(struct ssh *ssh)
1673{
1674 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
1675 Identity *id;
1676
1677 if (authctxt->agent_fd != -1) {
1678 ssh_close_authentication_socket(authctxt->agent_fd);
1679 authctxt->agent_fd = -1;
1680 }
1681 for (id = TAILQ_FIRST(&authctxt->keys); id;
1682 id = TAILQ_FIRST(&authctxt->keys)) {
1683 TAILQ_REMOVE(&authctxt->keys, id, next);
1684 sshkey_free(id->key);
1685 free(id->filename);
1686 free(id);
1687 }
1688}

1690static void
1691pubkey_reset(Authctxt *authctxt)
1692{
1693 Identity *id;
1694
1695 TAILQ_FOREACH(id, &authctxt->keys, next)
1696 id->tried = 0;
1697}

1699static int
1700try_identity(Identity *id)
1701{
1702 if (!id->key)
1703 return (0);
1704 if (sshkey_type_plain(id->key->type) == KEY_RSA &&
1705 (datafellows & SSH_BUG_RSASIGMD5) != 0) {
1706 debug("Skipped %s key %s for RSA/MD5 server",
1707 sshkey_type(id->key), id->filename);
1708 return (0);
1709 }
1710 return 1;
1711}
1712
1713static int
1714userauth_pubkey(struct ssh *ssh)
1715{
1716 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
1717 Identity *id;
1718 int sent = 0;
1719 char *ident;
1720
1721 while ((id = TAILQ_FIRST(&authctxt->keys))) {
1722 if (id->tried++)
1723 return (0);
1724 /* move key to the end of the queue */
1725 TAILQ_REMOVE(&authctxt->keys, id, next);
1726 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&authctxt->keys, id, next);
1727 /*
1728 * send a test message if we have the public key. for
1729 * encrypted keys we cannot do this and have to load the
1730 * private key instead
1731 */
1732 if (id->key != NULL) {
1733 if (try_identity(id)) {
1734 ident = format_identity(id);
1735 debug("Offering public key: %s", ident);
1736 free(ident);
1737 sent = send_pubkey_test(ssh, id);
1738 }
1739 } else {
1740 debug("Trying private key: %s", id->filename);
1741 id->key = load_identity_file(id);
1742 if (id->key != NULL) {
1743 if (try_identity(id)) {
1744 id->isprivate = 1;
1745 sent = sign_and_send_pubkey(ssh, id);
1746 }
1747 sshkey_free(id->key);
1748 id->key = NULL;
1749 id->isprivate = 0;
1750 }
1751 }
1752 if (sent)
1753 return (sent);
1754 }
1755 return (0);
1756}

1758/*
1759 * Send userauth request message specifying keyboard-interactive method.
1760 */
1761static int
1762userauth_kbdint(struct ssh *ssh)
1763{
1764 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
1765 int r;
1766
1767 if (authctxt->attempt_kbdint++ >= options.number_of_password_prompts)
1768 return 0;
1769 /* disable if no SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_INFO_REQUEST has been seen */
1770 if (authctxt->attempt_kbdint > 1 && !authctxt->info_req_seen) {
1771 debug3("userauth_kbdint: disable: no info_req_seen");
1772 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_INFO_REQUEST, NULL);
1773 return 0;
1774 }
1775
1776 debug2("userauth_kbdint");
1777 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
1778 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
1779 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
1780 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
1781 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, "")) != 0 || /* lang */
1782 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, options.kbd_interactive_devices ?
1783 options.kbd_interactive_devices : "")) != 0 ||
1784 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0)
1785 fatal("%s: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1786
1787 ssh_dispatch_set(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_INFO_REQUEST, &input_userauth_info_req);
1788 return 1;
1789}
1790
1791/*
1792 * parse INFO_REQUEST, prompt user and send INFO_RESPONSE
1793 */
1794static int
1795input_userauth_info_req(int type, u_int32_t seq, struct ssh *ssh)
1796{
1797 Authctxt *authctxt = ssh->authctxt;
1798 char *name = NULL, *inst = NULL, *lang = NULL, *prompt = NULL;
1799 char *response = NULL;
1800 u_char echo = 0;
1801 u_int num_prompts, i;
1802 int r;
1803
1804 debug2("input_userauth_info_req");
1805
1806 if (authctxt == NULL)
1807 fatal("input_userauth_info_req: no authentication context");
1808
1809 authctxt->info_req_seen = 1;
1810
1811 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &name, NULL)) != 0 ||
1812 (r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &inst, NULL)) != 0 ||
1813 (r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &lang, NULL)) != 0)
1814 goto out;
1815 if (strlen(name) > 0)
1816 logit("%s", name);
1817 if (strlen(inst) > 0)
1818 logit("%s", inst);
1819
1820 if ((r = sshpkt_get_u32(ssh, &num_prompts)) != 0)
1821 goto out;
1822 /*
1823 * Begin to build info response packet based on prompts requested.
1824 * We commit to providing the correct number of responses, so if
1825 * further on we run into a problem that prevents this, we have to
1826 * be sure and clean this up and send a correct error response.
1827 */
1828 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_INFO_RESPONSE)) != 0 ||
1829 (r = sshpkt_put_u32(ssh, num_prompts)) != 0)
1830 goto out;
1831
1832 debug2("input_userauth_info_req: num_prompts %d", num_prompts);
1833 for (i = 0; i < num_prompts; i++) {
1834 if ((r = sshpkt_get_cstring(ssh, &prompt, NULL)) != 0 ||
1835 (r = sshpkt_get_u8(ssh, &echo)) != 0)
1836 goto out;
1837 response = read_passphrase(prompt, echo ? RP_ECHO : 0);
1838 if ((r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, response)) != 0)
1839 goto out;
1840 freezero(response, strlen(response));
1841 free(prompt);
1842 response = prompt = NULL;
1843 }
1844 /* done with parsing incoming message. */
1845 if ((r = sshpkt_get_end(ssh)) != 0 ||
1846 (r = sshpkt_add_padding(ssh, 64)) != 0)
1847 goto out;
1848 r = sshpkt_send(ssh);
1849 out:
1850 if (response)
1851 freezero(response, strlen(response));
1852 free(prompt);
1853 free(name);
1854 free(inst);
1855 free(lang);
1856 return r;
1857}

1859static int
1860ssh_keysign(struct ssh *ssh, struct sshkey *key, u_char **sigp, size_t *lenp,
1861 const u_char *data, size_t datalen)
1862{
1863 struct sshbuf *b;
1864 struct stat st;
1865 pid_t pid;
1866 int i, r, to[2], from[2], status;
1867 int sock = ssh_packet_get_connection_in(ssh);
1868 u_char rversion = 0, version = 2;
1869 void (*osigchld)(int);
1870
1871 *sigp = NULL;
1872 *lenp = 0;
1873
1874 if (stat(_PATH_SSH_KEY_SIGN, &st) < 0) {
1875 error("%s: not installed: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1876 return -1;
1877 }
1878 if (fflush(stdout) != 0) {
1879 error("%s: fflush: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1880 return -1;
1881 }
1882 if (pipe(to) < 0) {
1883 error("%s: pipe: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1884 return -1;
1885 }
1886 if (pipe(from) < 0) {
1887 error("%s: pipe: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1888 return -1;
1889 }
1890 if ((pid = fork()) < 0) {
1891 error("%s: fork: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1892 return -1;
1893 }
1894 osigchld = signal(SIGCHLD, SIG_DFL);
1895 if (pid == 0) {
1896 /* keep the socket on exec */
1897 fcntl(sock, F_SETFD, 0);
1898 close(from[0]);
1899 if (dup2(from[1], STDOUT_FILENO) < 0)
1900 fatal("%s: dup2: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1901 close(to[1]);
1902 if (dup2(to[0], STDIN_FILENO) < 0)
1903 fatal("%s: dup2: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1904 close(from[1]);
1905 close(to[0]);
1906 /* Close everything but stdio and the socket */
1907 for (i = STDERR_FILENO + 1; i < sock; i++)
1908 close(i);
1909 if (closefrom(sock + 1) < 0)
1910 fatal("%s: closefrom: %s", __func__, strerror(errno));
1911 debug3("%s: [child] pid=%ld, exec %s",
1912 __func__, (long)getpid(), _PATH_SSH_KEY_SIGN);
1913 execl(_PATH_SSH_KEY_SIGN, _PATH_SSH_KEY_SIGN, (char *)NULL);
1914 fatal("%s: exec(%s): %s", __func__, _PATH_SSH_KEY_SIGN,
1915 strerror(errno));
1916 }
1917 close(from[1]);
1918 close(to[0]);
1919
1920 if ((b = sshbuf_new()) == NULL)
1921 fatal("%s: sshbuf_new failed", __func__);
1922 /* send # of sock, data to be signed */
1923 if ((r = sshbuf_put_u32(b, sock)) != 0 ||
1924 (r = sshbuf_put_string(b, data, datalen)) != 0)
1925 fatal("%s: buffer error: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1926 if (ssh_msg_send(to[1], version, b) == -1)
1927 fatal("%s: couldn't send request", __func__);
1928 sshbuf_reset(b);
1929 r = ssh_msg_recv(from[0], b);
1930 close(from[0]);
1931 close(to[1]);
1932 if (r < 0) {
1933 error("%s: no reply", __func__);
1934 goto fail;
1935 }
1936
1937 errno = 0;
1938 while (waitpid(pid, &status, 0) < 0) {
1939 if (errno != EINTR) {
1940 error("%s: waitpid %ld: %s",
1941 __func__, (long)pid, strerror(errno));
1942 goto fail;
1943 }
1944 }
1945 if (!WIFEXITED(status)) {
1946 error("%s: exited abnormally", __func__);
1947 goto fail;
1948 }
1949 if (WEXITSTATUS(status) != 0) {
1950 error("%s: exited with status %d",
1951 __func__, WEXITSTATUS(status));
1952 goto fail;
1953 }
1954 if ((r = sshbuf_get_u8(b, &rversion)) != 0) {
1955 error("%s: buffer error: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1956 goto fail;
1957 }
1958 if (rversion != version) {
1959 error("%s: bad version", __func__);
1960 goto fail;
1961 }
1962 if ((r = sshbuf_get_string(b, sigp, lenp)) != 0) {
1963 error("%s: buffer error: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
1964 fail:
1965 signal(SIGCHLD, osigchld);
1966 sshbuf_free(b);
1967 return -1;
1968 }
1969 signal(SIGCHLD, osigchld);
1970 sshbuf_free(b);
1971
1972 return 0;
1973}

1975static int
1976userauth_hostbased(struct ssh *ssh)
1977{
1978 Authctxt *authctxt = (Authctxt *)ssh->authctxt;
1979 struct sshkey *private = NULL;
1980 struct sshbuf *b = NULL;
1981 u_char *sig = NULL, *keyblob = NULL;
1982 char *fp = NULL, *chost = NULL, *lname = NULL;
1983 size_t siglen = 0, keylen = 0;
1984 int i, r, success = 0;
1985
1986 if (authctxt->ktypes == NULL) {
1987 authctxt->oktypes = xstrdup(options.hostbased_key_types);
1988 authctxt->ktypes = authctxt->oktypes;
1989 }
1990
1991 /*
1992 * Work through each listed type pattern in HostbasedKeyTypes,
1993 * trying each hostkey that matches the type in turn.
1994 */
1995 for (;;) {
1996 if (authctxt->active_ktype == NULL)
1997 authctxt->active_ktype = strsep(&authctxt->ktypes, ",");
1998 if (authctxt->active_ktype == NULL ||
1999 *authctxt->active_ktype == '\0')
2000 break;
2001 debug3("%s: trying key type %s", __func__,
2002 authctxt->active_ktype);
2003
2004 /* check for a useful key */
2005 private = NULL;
2006 for (i = 0; i < authctxt->sensitive->nkeys; i++) {
2007 if (authctxt->sensitive->keys[i] == NULL ||
2008 authctxt->sensitive->keys[i]->type == KEY_UNSPEC)
2009 continue;
2010 if (match_pattern_list(
2011 sshkey_ssh_name(authctxt->sensitive->keys[i]),
2012 authctxt->active_ktype, 0) != 1)
2013 continue;
2014 /* we take and free the key */
2015 private = authctxt->sensitive->keys[i];
2016 authctxt->sensitive->keys[i] = NULL;
2017 break;
2018 }
2019 /* Found one */
2020 if (private != NULL)
2021 break;
2022 /* No more keys of this type; advance */
2023 authctxt->active_ktype = NULL;
2024 }
2025 if (private == NULL) {
2026 free(authctxt->oktypes);
2027 authctxt->oktypes = authctxt->ktypes = NULL;
2028 authctxt->active_ktype = NULL;
2029 debug("No more client hostkeys for hostbased authentication.");
2030 goto out;
2031 }
2032
2033 if ((fp = sshkey_fingerprint(private, options.fingerprint_hash,
2034 SSH_FP_DEFAULT)) == NULL) {
2035 error("%s: sshkey_fingerprint failed", __func__);
2036 goto out;
2037 }
2038 debug("%s: trying hostkey %s %s",
2039 __func__, sshkey_ssh_name(private), fp);
2040
2041 /* figure out a name for the client host */
2042 lname = get_local_name(ssh_packet_get_connection_in(ssh));
2043 if (lname == NULL) {
2044 error("%s: cannot get local ipaddr/name", __func__);
2045 goto out;
2046 }
2047
2048 /* XXX sshbuf_put_stringf? */
2049 xasprintf(&chost, "%s.", lname);
2050 debug2("%s: chost %s", __func__, chost);
2051
2052 /* construct data */
2053 if ((b = sshbuf_new()) == NULL) {
2054 error("%s: sshbuf_new failed", __func__);
2055 goto out;
2056 }
2057 if ((r = sshkey_to_blob(private, &keyblob, &keylen)) != 0) {
2058 error("%s: sshkey_to_blob: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
2059 goto out;
2060 }
2061 if ((r = sshbuf_put_string(b, session_id2, session_id2_len)) != 0 ||
2062 (r = sshbuf_put_u8(b, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
2063 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
2064 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
2065 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
2066 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, sshkey_ssh_name(private))) != 0 ||
2067 (r = sshbuf_put_string(b, keyblob, keylen)) != 0 ||
2068 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, chost)) != 0 ||
2069 (r = sshbuf_put_cstring(b, authctxt->local_user)) != 0) {
2070 error("%s: buffer error: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
2071 goto out;
2072 }
2073
2074#ifdef DEBUG_PK
2075 sshbuf_dump(b, stderr);
2076#endif
2077 if ((r = ssh_keysign(ssh, private, &sig, &siglen,
2078 sshbuf_ptr(b), sshbuf_len(b))) != 0) {
2079 error("sign using hostkey %s %s failed",
2080 sshkey_ssh_name(private), fp);
2081 goto out;
2082 }
2083 if ((r = sshpkt_start(ssh, SSH2_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST)) != 0 ||
2084 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->server_user)) != 0 ||
2085 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->service)) != 0 ||
2086 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->method->name)) != 0 ||
2087 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, sshkey_ssh_name(private))) != 0 ||
2088 (r = sshpkt_put_string(ssh, keyblob, keylen)) != 0 ||
2089 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, chost)) != 0 ||
2090 (r = sshpkt_put_cstring(ssh, authctxt->local_user)) != 0 ||
2091 (r = sshpkt_put_string(ssh, sig, siglen)) != 0 ||
2092 (r = sshpkt_send(ssh)) != 0) {
2093 error("%s: packet error: %s", __func__, ssh_err(r));
2094 goto out;
2095 }
2096 success = 1;
2097
2098 out:
2099 if (sig != NULL)
2100 freezero(sig, siglen);
2101 free(keyblob);
2102 free(lname);
2103 free(fp);
2104 free(chost);
2105 sshkey_free(private);
2106 sshbuf_free(b);
2107
2108 return success;
2109}

2216/*
2217 * given auth method name, if configurable options permit this method fill
2218 * in auth_ident field and return true, otherwise return false.
2219 */
2220static int
2221authmethod_is_enabled(Authmethod *method)
2222{
2223 if (method == NULL)
2224 return 0;
2225 /* return false if options indicate this method is disabled */
2226 if (method->enabled == NULL || *method->enabled == 0)
2227 return 0;
2228 /* return false if batch mode is enabled but method needs interactive mode */
2229 if (method->batch_flag != NULL && *method->batch_flag != 0)
2230 return 0;
2231 return 1;
2232}

2234static Authmethod *
2235authmethod_lookup(const char *name)
2236{
2237 Authmethod *method = NULL;
2238 if (name != NULL)
2239 for (method = authmethods; method->name != NULL; method++)
2240 if (strcmp(name, method->name) == 0)
2241 return method;
2242 debug2("Unrecognized authentication method name: %s", name ? name : "NULL");
2243 return NULL;
2244}

2246/* XXX internal state */
2247static Authmethod *current = NULL;
2248static char *supported = NULL;
2249static char *preferred = NULL;
2250
2251/*
2252 * Given the authentication method list sent by the server, return the
2253 * next method we should try. If the server initially sends a nil list,
2254 * use a built-in default list.
2255 */
2256static Authmethod *
2257authmethod_get(char *authlist)
2258{
2259 char *name = NULL;
2260 u_int next;
2261
2262 /* Use a suitable default if we're passed a nil list. */
2263 if (authlist == NULL || strlen(authlist) == 0)
2264 authlist = options.preferred_authentications;
2265
2266 if (supported == NULL || strcmp(authlist, supported) != 0) {
2267 debug3("start over, passed a different list %s", authlist);
2268 free(supported);
2269 supported = xstrdup(authlist);
2270 preferred = options.preferred_authentications;
2271 debug3("preferred %s", preferred);
2272 current = NULL;
2273 } else if (current != NULL && authmethod_is_enabled(current))
2274 return current;
2275
2276 for (;;) {
2277 if ((name = match_list(preferred, supported, &next)) == NULL) {
2278 debug("No more authentication methods to try.");
2279 current = NULL;
2280 return NULL;
2281 }
2282 preferred += next;
2283 debug3("authmethod_lookup %s", name);
2284 debug3("remaining preferred: %s", preferred);
2285 if ((current = authmethod_lookup(name)) != NULL &&
2286 authmethod_is_enabled(current)) {
2287 debug3("authmethod_is_enabled %s", name);
2288 debug("Next authentication method: %s", name);
2289 free(name);
2290 return current;
2291 }
2292 free(name);
2293 }
2294}

2296static char *
2297authmethods_get(void)
2298{
2299 Authmethod *method = NULL;
2300 struct sshbuf *b;
2301 char *list;
2302 int r;
2303
2304 if ((b = sshbuf_new()) == NULL)
2305 fatal("%s: sshbuf_new failed", __func__);
2306 for (method = authmethods; method->name != NULL; method++) {
2307 if (authmethod_is_enabled(method)) {
2308 if ((r = sshbuf_putf(b, "%s%s",

2310 fatal("%s: buffer error: %s",

2312 }
2313 }
2314 if ((list = sshbuf_dup_string(b)) == NULL)
2315 fatal("%s: sshbuf_dup_string failed", __func__);
2316 sshbuf_free(b);
